physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Physical examination revealed expiratory, as well as inspiratory, stridor throughout both lung fields without rales or ronchi.

physical_examinations.vital_signs: Blood glucose level: 210 mg/dL, Blood urea nitrogen level: 50 mg/dL, Creatinine level: 2.4 mg/dL.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Forced expiratory volume in 1 second: 20%, Forced vital capacity: 86%, Forced expiratory volume in 1 second/forced vital capacity: 70.3%, Diffusion capacity: 84% of predicted values. Resting oxygen saturation was normal. Configuration of the flow-volume loop was suggestive of variable intrathoracic upper airway obstruction, with reduction in peak expiratory flow to 22% of predicted value.
